- 'pristine items' refers to items in a "New" condition; 
- 'concluded sale' refers to an auction with a status of 'Closed'; 
- 'admirers' refers to bidders who have placed a bid; 
- 'suitor' refers to a bidder who has placed at least one bid.

sql:
SELECT seller_name, seller_total_sales
FROM sellers
ORDER BY seller_total_sales DESC;

SELECT auction_id, final_bid_amount
FROM auctions
WHERE num_bidders = (SELECT MAX(num_bidders) FROM auctions);

